.TH "rdma_dev_access_netns" 9 "rdma_dev_access_netns" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rdma_dev_access_netns \- Return whether an rdma device can be accessed from a specified net namespace or not.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" rdma_dev_access_netns
.BI "(const struct ib_device *dev "  ","
.BI "const struct net *net "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Pointer to rdma device which needs to be checked
.IP "net" 12
Pointer to net namesapce for which access to be checked
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
When the rdma device is in shared mode, it ignores the net namespace.
When the rdma device is exclusive to a net namespace, rdma device net
namespace is checked against the specified one.
